<TEXT>
emperor hirohitos temperature remained high but 
no further bleeding was reported wednesday morning the 17th day 
since the 87yearold monarch fell seriously ill 
he has been bedridden since internal hemorrhaging caused him to 
vomit blood sept 19 and has continued intermittently to discharge 
an unspecified amount of blood 
kenji maeda head of general affairs division of the imperial 
household agency told reporters in the latest report that the 
emperor had no discharge of blood and remained in stable 
condition 
he said the monarchs temperature was 9896 wednesday morning 
compared with 100 tuesday evening the reading was still 
considerably higher than his normal reading of 959 
his heir and other royal relatives visited hirohito on tuesday 
the man who has reigned longer than any other living monarch 
palace officials said hirohito watched a 15minute television 
drama tuesday afternoon 
relatives said he talked about the olympic games which just 
ended in south korea 
some reports have said hirohito has intestinal cancer palace 
officials neither confirmed nor denied the reports and have asked 
journalists not to speculate 
other reports say he also has acute jaundice and a 
malfunctioning kidney 
since his condition worsened two weeks ago hirohito has been 
unable to take food or liquids except for two small ice cubes and a 
few spoonfuls of porridge 
among those visiting him tuesday were crown prince akihito 
crown princess michiko and their children prince hiro prince aya 
and princess nori 
akihito 54 has assumed his fathers duties which are largely 
ceremonial 
</TEXT>
