<TEXT>
libyas foreign minister on tuesday 
repeated his countrys demand for compensation from america for the 
us air raids in 1986 on tripoli and benghazi 
gadallah azouz eltalhy told the general assembly may i 
remind you of the flagrant barbaric aggression perpetrated by the 
united states of america in the spring of 1986 
this aggression was condemned by world public opinion at the 
time and by this distinguished assembly which recognized the 
right of our people to receive appropriate compensation for the 
losses incurred he said he did not mention any specific amount 
us warplanes attacked the two libyan cities on april 15 1986 
after the reagan administration accused the regime of libyan leader 
moammar gadhafi of supporting international terrorism 
libyan authorities said 41 people perished in the raids and the 
attacks were aimed at killing gadhafi they denied the allegation 
that libya had supported terrorists 
in november 1986 the general assembly passed a resolution 7928 
condemning the raids libya then asked the security council for a 
similar resolution but america britain and france vetoed it 
as the american attack against libya is one of the items on 
the general assembly agenda this session we call upon all 
peaceloving states to reiterate their condemnation of this 
aggression and to support libyas demand for compensation 
eltalhy told the assembly 
