<TEXT>
the life of the miniskirt on the milan 
runway has proved to be as brief as its hemline 
only a year after italian designers bared the leg right up to 
the hip bone they are covering it again straight down to the 
ankle 
for the most part the new look for spring and summer 1989 is 
long and loose with a myriad of pants and long skirts creating a 
softer quieter mood than in the past few seasons 
the change was most evident at gianni versace known for his 
hiphugging styles and soaring hemlines 
in his show monday versace concentrated heavily on pants in his 
subdued summer collection either cropping them at the calf or 
letting them flow softly to the ankle waistlines tended to be high 
or placed comfortably on the hip when he wasnt showing pants he 
wrapped his models in demure loose anklelength skirts buttoned 
down the front 
on the whole the versace collection concentrated on a 
sophisticated summer look which ignored the lighthearted outfits 
prevalent in the first two days of the fiveday showings although 
he presented several shades such as tangerine lemon and lime most 
of the collection was in black and white 
except for several trim city pants suits with small jacket and 
tapered mantailored trousers the emphasis was on nighttime his 
favorite evening look was a oneshouldered chiffon gown adorned 
with a single tassel draped over the back on a long silk cord huge 
gold and silver bracelets and earrings added extra glamor 
keith varty for byblos who opened the monday showings at the 
milan trade fair grounds opted for the ethnic mood which has 
prevailed in most of the collections he brings his summer client 
to the shores of copacabana in a brightly colored carioca skirt and 
flowers in her hair or drops her off in the virgin islands in 
loose cropped pants and jungle printed camisole 
there wasnt much novelty in the outfits copied stitch and 
ruffle from their native countries but the funloving styles and 
bright tropical shades created a carefree mood which is what summer 
is all about 
also on mondays calendar was the enfant terrible of italian 
fashion franco moschino who delights in taking the fashion crowd 
for a ride at least at his show in past seasons he spoofed 
chanel by loading his models with gold chains poked fun at 
jeanpaul gaultier by putting everything but the kitchen sink on 
hats and ridiculed the sexier outfits of his italian colleagues by 
parading real underwear down the runway 
his latest gimmick was to show his own clothes from past seasons 
as if they were his new styles and to haul the models off the 
runway to be replaced by a large video screen with the words 
what we really need is a change written in big letters 
</TEXT>
