japanese police and immigration authorities 
arrested a record 7196 foreigners in the first six months of this 
year for violating immigration laws by working in japan the 
immigration office said today 
the number of violators from januaryjune was up 24 percent from 
the previous record of 5802 in the corresponding period of 1987 
an official of the immigration office said 
those arrested this year compared to the same period last year 
included 3013 filipinos down from 4436 1432 bangladeshis 
sharply up from 139 1169 pakistanis up from 288 727 thais up 
from 561 and 447 south koreans up from 81 all compared with the 
like period of 1987 
most of those arrested were deported the official said 
last year 11307 foreigners were arrested throughout the nation 
for working illegally 
