traditional political tactics dictate that a candidate avoid 
public disputes with a staff aide to a rival and that the man at 
the top of the ticket not be drawn into a dispute with someone 
further down 
the reason is obvious as walter f mondale found out in 1984 
when he sought to brutalize bush for offering blind loyalty to 
ronald reagan bush then the understudy on the gop ticket was 
delighted to maintain a public quarrel with the leading democrat 
leaving reagan free to remain above the fray 
