<TEXT>
social democratic prime minister ingvar 
carlsson installed his new government tuesday pledging lower 
taxes six weeks annual vacation for workers and a streamlined 
national defense 
his policy speech to parliament expanded on his campaign themes 
for last months election in which his party retained office as a 
minority government 
the social democrats have led sweden for 50 of the last 56 
years they took 156 of the 379 seats in parliament and govern with 
the tacit support of the communist party which holds 21 seats 
carlsson said every worker male or female will be entitled to 
double the current amount of parental leave by 1991 and may take 
18 months off work with full pay 
new legislation will guarantee everyone an extra week off for a 
total of six weeks annual vacation a privilege now enjoyed only by 
workers over 40 years of age 
carlsson who inherited the premiership after olof palmes 1986 
assassination introduced a largely unchanged 21member cabinet 
one addition was laila freivalds 46 a latvianborn woman who 
becomes justice minister 
carlsson promised to introduce a bill to lower the tax rate next 
year by 3 percent easing a situation which discourages overtime 
and slows the national growth rate 
the top tax bracket would drop to 72 percent an average swede 
with a salary of 23000 will lose 47 percent of his paycheck to 
taxes instead of half of it a finance ministry spokesman said 
lack of workers and the low level of saving is limiting 
growth pushing up prices and costs carlsson said specific 
measures will be implemented to increase saving and make better 
use of peoples will to work 
corporate taxes and the 235 percent value added tax a form of 
indirect sales tax will be reviewed he said 
the prime minister moved to defuse criticism from his armed 
forces commander and the rightwing opposition that the military 
lacked funds to carry out government defense strategy 
the army will be reformed and made more efficient he said 
without elaboration the policy of neutrality is supported by a 
strong defense to protect our independence 
