bladder cancer at an early treatable stage and may be useful in 
other kinds of cancer the national cancer institute announced 
tuesday 
existing tests to diagnose bladder cancer involving removal of 
some tissue pose some risk and are often painful and they 
sometimes do not detect the cancer until it has spread and can no 
longer be cured the cancer institute said 
one of the researchers who developed the urine test said it 
detects a protein associated with the spread of tumors the test 
has also been used to detect kidney cancer prostate cancer and a 
