subsidiary that will have complete autonomy from the japanse 
parent that separation is required by the pentagon because the 
unit is a major defense contractor 
c david ferguson 46 a 25year veteran of the company was 
named monday to replace mcdonald he was most recently executive 
vice president of goulds materials and components division 
the company also announced today it was moving its corporate 
headquarters from the chicago suburb of rolling meadows to 
eastlake ohio near cleveland where most of goulds remaining 
properties are located the relocation is expected to be completed 
in 1990 and include the addition of about 25 jobs 
gould already has divested itself of most of its defense units 
it continues to own navcom which is tied up in a dispute with the 
federal government over a fixed pricing contract 
