chrysler motors corp and a japanese 
automobile distribution company have formed a joint venture to 
market jeeps and other chrysler products in japan the no 3 us 
automaker said today 
the agreement is between chrysler motors the carmaking arm of 
chrysler corp and j osawa amp co ltd of tokyo which has been 
distributing alfa romeo in japan chrysler said in a news release 
the jeep which chrysler acquired in its merger with american 
motors corp is one of the bestselling sports utility vehicles in 
the united states 
osawa a subsidiary the seibu saison group of automobile 
distributors will hold 85 percent of the new chrysler japan sales 
ltd chrysler will hold the remaining 15 percent 
chrysler japan sales will import 1200 to 1300 vehicles during 
its first year chrysler said the company will ship to japan its 
chrysler new yorker landau chrysler lebaron coupe and convertible 
dodge daytona es turbo sports coupe and jeep cherokee and wrangler 
models 
the vehicles will be sold in chryslerjeep dealerships in tokyo 
osaka and nagoya immediately during the next year about 30 
independent dealers will be used in other markets 
chrysler and jeep vehicles had been sold in japan previously 
through two independent distributors which will continue to 
operate through the chrysler japan sales dealer network the 
company said 
although the market for imported cars in japan is small today 
it reached a record level in 1987 and will grow substantially in 
the next five years said michael hammes vice president for 
international operations of chrysler motors 
according to figures from the japanese automobile importers 
association inc 97750 cars were imported to japan in 1987 up 43 
percent from the 68357 cars brought in the year before 
the number of imported cars in japan has grown steadily since 
1984 the importers association figures show 
