ltv corp said today it plans to sell ltv 
steel cos ohiobased bar division in line with its 
reorganization under federal bankruptcy laws 
raymond a hay ltvs chairman and chief executive officer said 
the company wants its steel division to concentrate on flat rolled 
and tubular products 
we have concluded that ltv steel must focus its resources on 
its large modern flatrolled facilities in order to maintain a 
leadership position in production of high quality value added 
steels for critical engineering applications hay said 
ltv steel based in cleveland is a branch of dallasbased ltv 
corp a diversified manufacturing company also involved in 
aerospace defense and energy products 
hay said the companys thirdquarter results will include a 
substantial charge against earnings as a result of todays move 
the bar division located in canton ohio employs about 5400 
workers who produce approximately 12 million tons of steel 
annually 
