us companies are getting a growing proportion 
of their total sales from exports according to a survey released 
tuesday by the conference board 
exports from the united states accounted for 10 percent or more 
of total sales at 49 percent of the surveyed companies compared to 
about 40 percent of the surveyed companies in 1986 the conference 
board said 
exports accounted for 20 percent or more of the sales in 19 
percent of the companies up from 14 percent in 1986 
the survey is based on responses from the 277 companies that 
answered the survey out of the 1800 manufacturers that were 
approached the margin of error is 3 or 4 percentage points 
according to james greene who compiled the survey 
the export gains seem likely to continue greene said however 
he said us companies are also increasing their overseas 
investments those investments rose about 18 percent in 1987 to 35 
billion he said 
