the house banking committee voted 428 tuesday 
to abolish the muchcriticized federal agency created to manage and 
dispose of the assets of insolvent savings institutions 
the federal asset disposition association was formed by the 
federal home loan bank board in 1985 to assist the federal savings 
and loan insurance corp in the management of acquired assets 
fada has been accused by members of congress of favoritism 
conflicts of interest and mismanagement of the 39 billion in 
loans and real estate in its care 
the bill similar to a section of the omnibus banking 
legislation approved by the house in august would assign fadas 
activities to fslic since the wideranging banking bill has run 
into trouble and may not be approved before congress adjourns this 
month a freestanding measure has a better chance of being passed 
reps paul kanjorski dpa and tom mcmillen dmd introduced 
the legsilation which would dismantle fada within 60 days and 
return its functions to fslic the government insurance fund that 
backs savings and loan deposits up to 100000 
rep fernand j st germain dri banking committee chairman 
said the panel has been investigating fada a quasipublic agency 
for the past 15 months 
our findings clearly establish that this agency has become a 
wasteful bureaucracy lacking in accountability and providing an 
inefficient means of disposing of property acquired from failed 
savings and loan associations he said high salaries big 
expense accounts and cialike secrecy have become the agencys 
claims to fame during its threeyear existence 
he quoted the general accounting office in a draft report not 
yet released as concluding that fadas functions are nonessential 
the gao the investigative arm of congress said in 
conclusion we found no compelling evidence that fada is essential 
to the management and disposition of assets acquired by fslic 
such functions could be done by a combination of other private 
sector asset management firms receivership employees and fslic 
headquarters and regional employees the gao said 
